	<a name="faq1"></a>
	<b>Who made this site?</b><br>
	<br>
	City Creator is a joint project by <a href="mailto:denise@citycreator.com">Denise Wilton</a> (also known as Pep) and <a href="mailto:cal@citycreator.com">Cal Henderson</a>. Denise came up with the original idea and design, and Cal helped the idea along and made it all come to life by programming it.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq8"></a>
	<b>Why do I need to register to send an ecard?</b><br>
	<br>
	We require you to register for a few reasons. Firstly, it cuts down abuse of the system. Secondly, it means we can let you save older cities and work on them later. Thirdly, it means we can let you share cities, so you can collaborate with your friends.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq9"></a>
	<b>Why do you ask for my email address?</b><br>
	<br>
	We ask you for your email address so that we can email you your password, should you forget it. We also use it to address any ecards you send.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq16"></a>
	<b>Are you going to sell my personal details?</b><br>
	<br>
	No. This site complies with the Data Protection Act (1998). To see any details we have stored about you, simply send an email to <a href="mailto:cal@citycreator.com" class="white">cal@citycreator.com</a>. If you would like your account to be removed from our systems, just ask.<br>
<br>
We will not sell any information about any users. We couldn't find anyone who would pay us enough anyway.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq6"></a>
	<b>Can you add a building for me?</b><br>
	<br>
	These are the first of many cities planned by the City Creator Corporation. We'll soon be building more cities all over the world - and that's where you come in!<br>
<br>
If you have an idea for a city, a building, an object or would just like to get in touch, then drop us an email: <a href="mailto:cal@citycreator.com">cal@citycreator.com</a><br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq19"></a>
	<b>Can you make the pieces "rotatable"?</b><br>
	<br>
	To "rotate" the pieces would mean to design 2 to 4 versions of each piece,
so that you could select an orientation. Since each piece takes so long to 
design, and we only have limited time and space, we only offer some pieces
with more than one orientation. We try to make enough road, wall and path 
pieces to make any layout you want - with buildings it's a little more 
difficult, and we try to give as many alternatives of each as we can whilst
still having a good selection of different buildings.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
