	<a name="faq13"></a>
	<b>Can I use a city I created as my desktop wallpaper?</b><br>
	<br>
	Yes! Once you have saved your city (by clicking on "Save &amp; send"), go to the <a href="members.city" class="white">members page</a> and click on the thumbnail of it. In the window that pops up, right-click on the image of your city and choose "Set as Background/Wallpaper".<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq20"></a>
	<b>Can I use a city I created on my website?</b><br>
	<br>
	We allow use of the cities on 
non-commercial sites and weblogs. If you'd like to use our graphics on 
a commercial site or for an ad campaign, please get in touch and we can 
quote for custom built sites or illustrations.<br>
<br>
To use a city on your personal site, follow the instructions for using it as wallpaper above. If you use a city creator city on your site, we'd appriciate a link back to citycreator.com. And you can <a href="mailto:cal@citycreator.com">mail us</a> to say you've used a city!<br>
<br>
If you want to use a city you created in a print publication or on television, then please include a credit and send us a copy!<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq2"></a>
	<b>Why do the pieces disappear when I drag them?</b><br>
	<br>
	You're using IE6 on a PC, right? It's because the people who made IE6 were on crack. Choose "Tools" -&gt; "Internet Options..." from the menu. Click on the "Settings..." button, and change "Check for newer versions of stored pages:" from "Every visit to the page" to "Automatically". Click the "OK" button to close the window, then "OK" again to close the other window.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq3"></a>
	<b>Why doesn't this site work on my browser?</b><br>
	<br>
	Because your browser doesn't support the relevant standards. Try a recent version of Internet Explorer, Mozilla or Netscape.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq18"></a>
	<b>Why don't any/all the pieces appear in the palettes on the left?</b><br>
	<br>
	This looks like a bug with IE6's cacheing.

Make sure thae page has finished loading before you click anywhere in the 
window. If the little animation in the top right corner is still moving, 
or the progress bar in the status bar at the bottom of the window is still 
moving then the page hasn't fully loaded.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq4"></a>
	<b>How does this site work?</b><br>
	<br>
	The pages use HTML and CSS with GIF graphics. The drag-and-drop interface was built using ECMAScript (Javascript) and the DOM (Document Object Model). The back end uses PHP and MySQL. The thumbnails are generated using GD and PNG's.<br>
	<br>
	<img src="images/white_line.gif" width="368" height="5"><br>
	<br>
	<a name="faq14"></a>
	<b>Hey! I went away and came back, but my city is still there!</b><br>
	<br>
	Yes. That's not really a question, is it now...<br>
<br>
We use cookies so you can continue building your city at a later date.<br>
